 balls and 2 blue balls.\n\nZia takes a ball from the bag at random.\n\nWrite down the letter from the probability scale that shows the probability that\n\n(a) Zia takes a green ball\n\n(b) Zia takes a yellow ball\n\n(c) Zia does not take a blue ball.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q06","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":6,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.7","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sequences","qtype":"sequences","g":"sequence","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q06","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"These are the first four terms of a sequence.\n\n\\[ 19 \\quad 26 \\quad 33 \\quad 40 \\]\n\n(a) (i) (b) Find the next term.\n\n    \n\n(c) Write down the term to term rule for this sequence.\n\n    \n\n(d) These are the first four terms of another sequence.\n\\[ -1 \\quad 2 \\quad 5 \\quad 8 \\]\nFind the $n$th term of this sequence.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":0},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1},{"label":"(d)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q07","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":7,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q07","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Simplify.\n\\[ 3p - t - p - 4t \\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q08","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":8,"marks":2,"topics":["Number","Mensuration"],"s":"1.3","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Powers and roots","qtype":"powers and roots","g":"indices","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q08","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"\\[ 61 \\quad 62 \\quad 63 \\quad 64 \\quad 65 \\quad 66 \\quad 67 \\quad 68 \\quad 69 \\]\n\nFrom the list of numbers, write down\n\n(a) a cube number\n\n(b) a prime number.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q09","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":9,"marks":5,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.3","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Scale drawings and bearings","qtype":"scale drawings and bearings","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q09","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The scale drawing shows the positions of town K and town L.\n\nThe scale is 1~cm represents 10~km.\n\n(a) Find the actual distance between town K and town L.\n\n(b) Measure the bearing of town L from town K.\n\n(c) Town M is 40~km from town L on a bearing of 140$^\\circ$.\n\nOn the scale drawing, mark the position of town M.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q10","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":10,"marks":2,"topics":["Mensuration"],"s":"5.4","d":1,"cat":"mensuration","topic":"Surface area and volume","qtype":"surface area and volume","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q10","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The surface area of a cube is 121.5~cm$^2$.\n\nCalculate the length of one side of the cube.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q11","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":11,"marks":4,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q11","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) \nThe diagram shows three lines meeting at a point.\n\nFind the value of $w$.\n\n(b) \n\n$BCD$ is an isosceles triangle.\n\n$ABC$ is a straight line.\n\nWork out the value of $y$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":3}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q12","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":12,"marks":1,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry"],"s":"3.6","d":1,"cat":"coord","topic":"Parallel lines","qtype":"parallel lines","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q12","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Write down the equation of a line parallel to the line $y = 2x$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q13","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":13,"marks":4,"topics":["Statistics"],"s":"9.3","d":1,"cat":"statistics","topic":"Averages and measures of spread","qtype":"averages and spread","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q13","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Each student in a class of 20 students records the number of coins in their pockets.\n\nThe table shows the results.\n\n\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n\\begin{tabular}{|l|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|}\n\\hline\nNumber of coins & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5 & 6 \\\\ \\hline\nFrequency       & 3 & 1 & 7 & 8 & 0 & 0 & 1 \\\\ \\hline\n\\end{tabular}\n\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\n(a) Find the median.\n\n(b) Calculate the mean.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":3}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","texHtml":"Each student in a class of 20 students records the number of coins in their pockets.\n\nThe table shows the results.\n\n<div class=\"pp-table-wrap\"><table class=\"pp-table\"><tr><th>Number of coins</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">0</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">1</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">2</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">3</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">4</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">5</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">6</th></tr><tr><td>Frequency</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">3</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">7</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">8</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">0</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">0</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">1</td></tr></table></div>\n\n\n(a) Find the median.\n\n(b) Calculate the mean."},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q14","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":14,"marks":1,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q14","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Expand \\quad $4(x - 3)$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q15","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":15,"marks":2,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q15","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Find the size of an interior angle of a regular 15-sided polygon.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q16","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":16,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q16","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Rio buys some pens.\n\nHe sells 63 pens, which is $\\frac{7}{9}$ of the pens he buys.\n\nWork out how many pens he buys.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q17","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":17,"marks":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q17","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Ed has $n$ books. \n\nSam has 3 times as many books as Ed. \n\nJane has 2 books fewer than Sam. \n\nThe total number of books is 54.\n\nUse this information to write down an equation and solve it to find the value of $n$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q18","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":18,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q18","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Without using a calculator, work out $2\\frac{1}{4} - 1\\frac{11}{12}$. \n\nYou must show all your working and give your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q19","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":19,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Probability"],"s":"1.2","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Sets","qtype":"sets and Venn diagrams","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q19","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$\\mathscr{E} = \\{ \\text{workers in an office} \\}$ \n\n$C = \\{ \\text{workers who drink coffee} \\}$ \n\n$T = \\{ \\text{workers who drink tea} \\}$\n\n47 people work in the office.\n\n32 people drink tea.\n\n(a) Complete the Venn diagram.\n\n(b) Write down $n(C \\cup T)$.\n\n(c) Work out the probability that a worker chosen at random does not drink coffee.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q20","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":20,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.9","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q20","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The weight, $w$ grams, of a box is 463.9 grams, correct to 1 decimal place.\n\nComplete the statement about the value of $w$.\n\n $\\le w <$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2024OctNov-Paper13-Q21","paper":"2024OctNov-Paper13","qnum":21,"marks":1,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.8","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Standard form","qtype":"standard form","g":"mixed","src":"0580/13/O/N/24 Q21","year":2024,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Calculate $(6.4 \\times 10^5) \\div (2.5 \\times 10^{-7})$. \n\nGive your answer in standard form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cog